The Matric results are coming out on 20 January 2022. University South Africa’s Linda Meyer spoke with eNCA's Mfundo Mabalane. Courtesy of #DStv403 JOHANNESBURG - Universities South Africa says it can accommodate 240,000 first year students at public universities. There are approximately 375,000 students eligible for placement. WATCH: Discussion | Vaccination mandatory in many universities Universities' South Africa's Linda Meyer said: “We know that from the Grade 12 results there will approximately 375,000 students eligible for higher education placement. "And public universities will be able to absorb in the region of 240,000 of those students into the university system that caters, with private and public higher education, for approximately 1.3 million students throughout the higher education system.”  